syntax
  netcat -<options> <ip address> <port | ports>

  options
    -z zero I/O "port scanning"
    -v | -vv verbose or very verbose
    -n no lookup or do not resolve ip addresses
    -w1 set time-out to 1
    -u use udp











scripts
TCP port scanning:
  # multiple hosts
  for i in {<start addr>..<end addr>}; do nc -nvzw1 <first three octects>$i <port | ports> 2>&1 & done | grep -E 'succ|open'

  # single host 
  nc -nzvw1 <ip address> <port | ports> 2>&1 | grep -E 'succ|open'

UDP port scanning:
  # multiple hosts
  for i in {<start addr>..<end addr>}; do nc -nuvzw1 <first three octects>$i <port | ports> 2>&1 & done | grep -E 'succ|open'
  
  # single host
  nc -nuzvw1 <ip address> <port | ports> 2>&1 | grep -E 'succ|open'

Banner grabbing:
  nc <ip address> <port number>
  
